00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:18.009 align:middle line:90%


00:00:18.009 --> 00:00:20.050 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Well,
welcome to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:20.050 --> 00:00:20.920 align:middle line:10%
I'm George Noory.

00:00:20.920 --> 00:00:22.878 align:middle line:10%
Now, regardless of the
side of the fence you're

00:00:22.878 --> 00:00:26.040 align:middle line:10%
on with climate change,
there's no kidding yourself,

00:00:26.040 --> 00:00:28.680 align:middle line:10%
the world is changing.

00:00:28.680 --> 00:00:32.290 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look
at our next guest.

00:00:32.290 --> 00:00:33.790 align:middle line:84%
>>FEMALE VOICE: The
idea that people

00:00:33.790 --> 00:00:35.990 align:middle line:84%
cause global warming
is just politically

00:00:35.990 --> 00:00:37.550 align:middle line:90%
motivated propaganda.

00:00:37.550 --> 00:00:40.350 align:middle line:84%
That's the opinion of
Tim Ball, a geographer

00:00:40.350 --> 00:00:42.660 align:middle line:90%
and historical climatologist.

00:00:42.660 --> 00:00:46.460 align:middle line:10%
After earning his PhD from
Queen Mary University of London

00:00:46.460 --> 00:00:49.820 align:middle line:10%
in 1983, Tim moved
to Canada, where

00:00:49.820 --> 00:00:54.000 align:middle line:10%
he taught at the University
of Winnipeg for over 25 years.

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.430 align:middle line:84%
Tim rejects the
scientific consensus,

00:00:56.430 --> 00:00:59.500 align:middle line:84%
arguing that carbon
dioxide isn't dangerous.

00:00:59.500 --> 00:01:01.140 align:middle line:90%
It's essential.

00:01:01.140 --> 00:01:03.300 align:middle line:84%
For the past decade,
Tim has waged

00:01:03.300 --> 00:01:06.990 align:middle line:84%
a war of ideas against the
environmental movement.

00:01:06.990 --> 00:01:09.540 align:middle line:10%
The author and co-author
of many papers,

00:01:09.540 --> 00:01:11.750 align:middle line:10%
he's also written a
book, "The Deliberate

00:01:11.750 --> 00:01:15.570 align:middle line:10%
Corruption of Climate
Science," now in paperback.

00:01:15.570 --> 00:01:19.080 align:middle line:84%
He'll explain that what you've
been told about the environment

00:01:19.080 --> 00:01:22.685 align:middle line:90%
is more swindle than science.

00:01:22.685 --> 00:01:25.540 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, Tim, you've
been explaining for years now

00:01:25.540 --> 00:01:29.420 align:middle line:84%
and sounding the alarm
that folks, what you think

00:01:29.420 --> 00:01:32.370 align:middle line:84%
and what you hear
about climate change

00:01:32.370 --> 00:01:35.270 align:middle line:90%
isn't necessarily the fact.

00:01:35.270 --> 00:01:38.180 align:middle line:84%
>>TIM BALL: More than isn't
necessary-- it isn't the facts.

00:01:38.180 --> 00:01:39.965 align:middle line:10%
It's spin.

00:01:39.965 --> 00:01:41.170 align:middle line:10%
It's for the media.

00:01:41.170 --> 00:01:42.370 align:middle line:10%
It's to get attention.

00:01:42.370 --> 00:01:46.740 align:middle line:10%
It's to persuade politicians
to pursue certain agendas,

00:01:46.740 --> 00:01:47.970 align:middle line:10%
political agendas.

00:01:47.970 --> 00:01:50.460 align:middle line:10%
And it's basically
to control people,

00:01:50.460 --> 00:01:52.975 align:middle line:10%
because that's what politics
is essentially all about.

00:01:52.975 --> 00:01:56.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: As I said
at the outset too,

00:01:56.110 --> 00:01:59.110 align:middle line:84%
there's no question that
the climate is changing.

00:01:59.110 --> 00:02:02.000 align:middle line:90%
Things are strange.

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:05.960 align:middle line:84%
This winter in most areas
has been very mild--

00:02:05.960 --> 00:02:08.770 align:middle line:84%
70 degree temperatures
in St. Louis,

00:02:08.770 --> 00:02:10.419 align:middle line:90%
where I go back and forth.

00:02:10.419 --> 00:02:13.590 align:middle line:90%
Denver, 70 degrees in February.

00:02:13.590 --> 00:02:15.450 align:middle line:90%
It's bizarre.

00:02:15.450 --> 00:02:17.260 align:middle line:84%
But these are
cycles, aren't they?

00:02:17.260 --> 00:02:20.390 align:middle line:84%
>>BALL: Well, it's not only
cycles, but it's not bizarre.

00:02:20.390 --> 00:02:23.820 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if you think
about it, like Fox News

00:02:23.820 --> 00:02:25.920 align:middle line:90%
has extreme weather.

00:02:25.920 --> 00:02:27.400 align:middle line:90%
Well, what's extreme weather?

00:02:27.400 --> 00:02:29.070 align:middle line:84%
A hurricane is not
extreme weather.

00:02:29.070 --> 00:02:29.980 align:middle line:90%
It's normal.

00:02:29.980 --> 00:02:30.780 align:middle line:90%
It's normal.

00:02:30.780 --> 00:02:33.070 align:middle line:84%
But of course, what they're
really talking about

00:02:33.070 --> 00:02:35.139 align:middle line:84%
is the damage it does
to people's lives.

00:02:35.139 --> 00:02:37.555 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things that
happened when they were saying,

00:02:37.555 --> 00:02:39.630 align:middle line:84%
oh, global warming's a
problem and hurricanes

00:02:39.630 --> 00:02:42.320 align:middle line:84%
are increasing, what was
really increasing what's

00:02:42.320 --> 00:02:45.070 align:middle line:84%
the cost of dealing with the
impact of hurricanes, not

00:02:45.070 --> 00:02:47.040 align:middle line:84%
the actual hurricanes
themselves.

00:02:47.040 --> 00:02:50.740 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
that creates this illusion

00:02:50.740 --> 00:02:54.400 align:middle line:84%
that things are getting worse
or they've never been this bad

00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:56.427 align:middle line:84%
is that it's like
when-- everybody's

00:02:56.427 --> 00:02:57.260 align:middle line:90%
had this experience.

00:02:57.260 --> 00:02:59.490 align:middle line:84%
You're introduced
to somebody, and it

00:02:59.490 --> 00:03:01.326 align:middle line:84%
seems like every
time you turn around,

00:03:01.326 --> 00:03:03.006 align:middle line:84%
there they are or
there their name is.

00:03:03.006 --> 00:03:04.380 align:middle line:84%
They were always
there, they were

00:03:04.380 --> 00:03:09.430 align:middle line:84%
just not part of your world or
your detection, if you want.

00:03:09.430 --> 00:03:13.400 align:middle line:84%
Now the media's caught on to
the global warming, the climate

00:03:13.400 --> 00:03:14.250 align:middle line:90%
change.

00:03:14.250 --> 00:03:18.620 align:middle line:84%
So every time there's a weather
event anywhere, it's reported

00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:21.740 align:middle line:84%
and it's presented as if it's
abnormal, when in fact it's

00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:23.120 align:middle line:90%
perfectly normal.

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:27.520 align:middle line:84%
So because the public don't
know how much climate changes

00:03:27.520 --> 00:03:31.670 align:middle line:84%
all the time, and
extremely, then they're

00:03:31.670 --> 00:03:35.240 align:middle line:84%
very easily fooled into
believing that a normal event

00:03:35.240 --> 00:03:36.040 align:middle line:90%
is abnormal.

00:03:36.040 --> 00:03:36.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:03:36.840 --> 00:03:38.430 align:middle line:90%
And that we're causing it.

00:03:38.430 --> 00:03:39.630 align:middle line:90%
>>BALL: Yeah, exactly.

00:03:39.630 --> 00:03:44.670 align:middle line:84%
And so it's the image that
they create in people's minds,

00:03:44.670 --> 00:03:46.040 align:middle line:90%
and they use those terms.

00:03:46.040 --> 00:03:48.610 align:middle line:84%
For example, the Greenpeace
report on global warming

00:03:48.610 --> 00:03:51.740 align:middle line:84%
back in 1999, they
said, carbon dioxide

00:03:51.740 --> 00:03:55.280 align:middle line:84%
is added to the atmosphere
naturally and unnaturally.

00:03:55.280 --> 00:03:57.650 align:middle line:90%
Well, what do they mean by that?

00:03:57.650 --> 00:03:59.350 align:middle line:90%
What's the unnatural?

00:03:59.350 --> 00:04:02.500 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is,
unnaturally is human.

00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:05.300 align:middle line:84%
Say, well, if that's true, then
if what humans do is unnatural,

00:04:05.300 --> 00:04:07.400 align:middle line:84%
does that mean
humans are unnatural?

00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:09.660 align:middle line:84%
And this is the game
that they're playing.

00:04:09.660 --> 00:04:11.450 align:middle line:84%
They know the public
don't understand

00:04:11.450 --> 00:04:13.900 align:middle line:84%
the history of climate,
how much it changes.

00:04:13.900 --> 00:04:18.260 align:middle line:84%
They also know that most of
them are terrified of science.

00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:20.779 align:middle line:84%
You can divide the population
up into 80% percent

00:04:20.779 --> 00:04:23.790 align:middle line:84%
that aren't students and 20%
that are science students.

00:04:23.790 --> 00:04:25.609 align:middle line:84%
And then amongst
that 20% of science,

00:04:25.609 --> 00:04:27.900 align:middle line:84%
the number that actually know
about climate and climate

00:04:27.900 --> 00:04:29.740 align:middle line:90%
science is very small.

00:04:29.740 --> 00:04:31.750 align:middle line:84%
And then it's very easy
to marginalize them.

00:04:31.750 --> 00:04:33.810 align:middle line:84%
So when somebody comes
along like me and says,

00:04:33.810 --> 00:04:35.660 align:middle line:84%
no, what's happening
is perfectly normal.

00:04:35.660 --> 00:04:38.980 align:middle line:84%
It's well within natural
variability of climate-- oh,

00:04:38.980 --> 00:04:43.020 align:middle line:84%
paid by the oil companies--
very easy to marginalize.

00:04:43.020 --> 00:04:46.620 align:middle line:84%
And you, in your programs,
know about how they do that.

00:04:46.620 --> 00:04:51.030 align:middle line:84%
For example, they'll create
a term to lump people in.

00:04:51.030 --> 00:04:53.940 align:middle line:84%
So for example, anybody who
asks anything about Obama's

00:04:53.940 --> 00:04:57.320 align:middle line:84%
paperwork was a
birther which meant,

00:04:57.320 --> 00:04:58.650 align:middle line:90%
you're one of those birthers.

00:04:58.650 --> 00:05:00.884 align:middle line:84%
You're marginalized
outside of society.

00:05:00.884 --> 00:05:02.175 align:middle line:90%
You're not mainstream thinking.

00:05:02.175 --> 00:05:03.000 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Exactly.

00:05:03.000 --> 00:05:06.800 align:middle line:84%
>>BALL: And so they did
that with the climate issue.

00:05:06.800 --> 00:05:10.030 align:middle line:84%
It started out as
global warming skeptic,

00:05:10.030 --> 00:05:13.200 align:middle line:84%
until we started to point out
that, if you're not a skeptic,

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:14.840 align:middle line:90%
you're not a scientist.

00:05:14.840 --> 00:05:16.700 align:middle line:90%
All scientists are skeptics.

00:05:16.700 --> 00:05:22.110 align:middle line:84%
Well then, as you know, warming
stopped happening around 1998,

00:05:22.110 --> 00:05:23.270 align:middle line:90%
really started.

00:05:23.270 --> 00:05:26.160 align:middle line:84%
And so then they
ran into a problem,

00:05:26.160 --> 00:05:27.930 align:middle line:84%
because people
were saying, you're

00:05:27.930 --> 00:05:29.513 align:middle line:84%
talking about global
warming and we're

00:05:29.513 --> 00:05:31.027 align:middle line:90%
having record cold winters.

00:05:31.027 --> 00:05:31.860 align:middle line:90%
The facts don't fit.

00:05:31.860 --> 00:05:32.680 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It doesn't make sense.

00:05:32.680 --> 00:05:33.805 align:middle line:90%
>>BALL: Doesn't make sense.

00:05:33.805 --> 00:05:37.680 align:middle line:84%
So then they switched to climate
change, which allowed them then

00:05:37.680 --> 00:05:38.480 align:middle line:90%
to incorporate--

00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:39.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It was broader.

00:05:39.980 --> 00:05:42.950 align:middle line:10%
>>BALL: But they also
changed the isolation

00:05:42.950 --> 00:05:45.670 align:middle line:10%
of those that questioned,
because now if you challenged

00:05:45.670 --> 00:05:47.770 align:middle line:10%
climate change,
you were a denier,

00:05:47.770 --> 00:05:50.080 align:middle line:10%
with of the Holocaust
connotations to that.

00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:53.499 align:middle line:84%
They upped the ante to isolate
anybody that dared question.

