And none of that's
turned out to be

00:10:10.390 --> 00:10:12.890 align:middle line:90%
true at all-- absolutely false.

00:10:12.890 --> 00:10:15.340 align:middle line:84%
But that was the
Malthusian idea.

00:10:15.340 --> 00:10:17.980 align:middle line:84%
Because Malthus said
that the population would

00:10:17.980 --> 00:10:19.890 align:middle line:90%
outgrow the food supply.

00:10:19.890 --> 00:10:22.410 align:middle line:84%
That's equally turned
out to be wrong.

00:10:22.410 --> 00:10:25.080 align:middle line:84%
And by the way, Malthus had
a great influence on science,

00:10:25.080 --> 00:10:29.490 align:middle line:84%
because Darwin took Malthus'
essays on population with him

00:10:29.490 --> 00:10:33.330 align:middle line:84%
to the Galapagos and said
they were the guiding

00:10:33.330 --> 00:10:36.291 align:middle line:84%
influence on his ideas about
the theory of evolution,

00:10:36.291 --> 00:10:37.540 align:middle line:90%
which is an interesting thing.

00:10:37.540 --> 00:10:40.860 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why, Tim, when we
talk about climate change,

00:10:40.860 --> 00:10:43.100 align:middle line:84%
regardless of the side
of the fence you're on,

00:10:43.100 --> 00:10:44.880 align:middle line:90%
why is it so argumentative?

00:10:44.880 --> 00:10:46.950 align:middle line:90%
Why is it so bitter?

00:10:46.950 --> 00:10:48.130 align:middle line:90%
Because I've seen it.

00:10:48.130 --> 00:10:50.830 align:middle line:84%
I mean, even during my
open line phone calls

00:10:50.830 --> 00:10:54.360 align:middle line:84%
on "Coast to Coast," if we
talk about climate change

00:10:54.360 --> 00:10:56.810 align:middle line:84%
or even when you're
on as a guest,

00:10:56.810 --> 00:10:59.960 align:middle line:84%
you'll get a handful
of people-- minute,

00:10:59.960 --> 00:11:04.240 align:middle line:84%
but they're so angry if you
don't believe it's man-made.

00:11:04.240 --> 00:11:05.050 align:middle line:90%
Why is that?

00:11:05.050 --> 00:11:07.750 align:middle line:84%
>>BALL: Well, because it's
not a scientific belief.

00:11:07.750 --> 00:11:10.280 align:middle line:84%
It's a political and
ideological belief.

00:11:10.280 --> 00:11:13.717 align:middle line:84%
Because what they argued
was the Club of Rome,

00:11:13.717 --> 00:11:15.300 align:middle line:84%
which promoted "The
Limits to Growth,"

00:11:15.300 --> 00:11:18.780 align:middle line:84%
and pushed the overpopulation of
Paul Ehrlich-- and by the way,

00:11:18.780 --> 00:11:20.640 align:middle line:84%
Obama's science
czar, John Holdren,

00:11:20.640 --> 00:11:23.524 align:middle line:84%
who published with
Paul Ehrlich--

00:11:23.524 --> 00:11:25.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --who wants
population control.

00:11:25.190 --> 00:11:27.480 align:middle line:84%
>>BALL: He wants population
control, exactly.

00:11:27.480 --> 00:11:32.470 align:middle line:84%
And so you read the Club
of Rome book, the 1994 book

00:11:32.470 --> 00:11:34.060 align:middle line:90%
by Alexander King.

00:11:34.060 --> 00:11:37.690 align:middle line:84%
And they say that we need
something to unite us.

00:11:37.690 --> 00:11:40.480 align:middle line:84%
In other words, we
need a global threat

00:11:40.480 --> 00:11:43.580 align:middle line:84%
that we can then use to say,
hey, this needs one world

00:11:43.580 --> 00:11:45.300 align:middle line:90%
government to deal with it.

00:11:45.300 --> 00:11:47.500 align:middle line:84%
You can't rely on
individual nations.

00:11:47.500 --> 00:11:49.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You gotta
do it as a whole.

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:49.800 align:middle line:90%
>>BALL: Yeah.

00:11:49.800 --> 00:11:53.080 align:middle line:84%
And then we need something--
so they listed some things.

00:11:53.080 --> 00:11:54.030 align:middle line:90%
They listed pollution.

00:11:54.030 --> 00:11:55.810 align:middle line:90%
They listed water resources.

00:11:55.810 --> 00:11:58.200 align:middle line:84%
And by the way, that's
going to be the next issue.

00:11:58.200 --> 00:12:00.500 align:middle line:84%
And then they say,
global warming.

00:12:00.500 --> 00:12:05.990 align:middle line:84%
And so Maurice Strong, who
just passed away in China,

00:12:05.990 --> 00:12:09.970 align:middle line:84%
and came from a socialist
family, his sister,

00:12:09.970 --> 00:12:14.090 align:middle line:84%
or his aunt, I should say,
Anna Strong, was a Marxist,

00:12:14.090 --> 00:12:16.660 align:middle line:84%
moved to communist
China in the 1930s,

00:12:16.660 --> 00:12:19.330 align:middle line:84%
and became an adviser
to Mao Tse-tung.

00:12:19.330 --> 00:12:22.180 align:middle line:84%
So they come from a very
socialist background.

00:12:22.180 --> 00:12:26.890 align:middle line:84%
And Strong, in an interview
in a wonderful book

00:12:26.890 --> 00:12:29.920 align:middle line:84%
by Elaine Dewar, who
was one of, like you,

00:12:29.920 --> 00:12:34.730 align:middle line:84%
one of the original true
investigative journalists--

00:12:34.730 --> 00:12:37.545 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to start with an idea,
but if I find that I'm wrong,

00:12:37.545 --> 00:12:39.990 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I'm going to flex it.

00:12:39.990 --> 00:12:42.260 align:middle line:84%
>>BALL: She wanted to
write a book praising

00:12:42.260 --> 00:12:45.810 align:middle line:84%
Canadian environmentalists, like
David Suzuki, Elizabeth May,

00:12:45.810 --> 00:12:48.980 align:middle line:90%
and so on, and Maury Strong.

00:12:48.980 --> 00:12:50.660 align:middle line:84%
Halfway through
her research, she

00:12:50.660 --> 00:12:54.380 align:middle line:84%
found out these people were more
corrupt than the people they

00:12:54.380 --> 00:12:55.710 align:middle line:90%
were attacking.

00:12:55.710 --> 00:12:58.980 align:middle line:84%
So she wrote the book, "Cloak
of Green" And about 20%

00:12:58.980 --> 00:13:01.680 align:middle line:84%
percent of the book is
devoted to Maury Strong.

00:13:01.680 --> 00:13:04.092 align:middle line:84%
And she said to Strong,
well, what's the problem?

00:13:04.092 --> 00:13:05.550 align:middle line:84%
He said, the problem
with the world

00:13:05.550 --> 00:13:08.000 align:middle line:84%
is the industrialized
nations, that they're

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:11.030 align:middle line:84%
destroying the planet, and
isn't it our responsibility

00:13:11.030 --> 00:13:11.871 align:middle line:90%
to get rid of them.

00:13:11.871 --> 00:13:13.370 align:middle line:84%
Now, he wasn't just
talking about it

00:13:13.370 --> 00:13:14.724 align:middle line:90%
from a pollution point of view.

00:13:14.724 --> 00:13:16.640 align:middle line:84%
He was talking about it
from the point of view

00:13:16.640 --> 00:13:19.037 align:middle line:84%
that they are using up resources
at a much greater risk.

00:13:19.037 --> 00:13:20.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: So let's wipe them out.

00:13:20.370 --> 00:13:21.742 align:middle line:90%
>>BALL: Let's wipe them out.

00:13:21.742 --> 00:13:22.700 align:middle line:90%
Let's think about that.

00:13:22.700 --> 00:13:23.760 align:middle line:90%
How would you do that?

00:13:23.760 --> 00:13:26.410 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that that's the
genius, or if you want,

00:13:26.410 --> 00:13:29.574 align:middle line:84%
the evil genius of these people,
is not only having the idea.

00:13:29.574 --> 00:13:30.990 align:middle line:84%
Because we all
have lots of ideas.

00:13:30.990 --> 00:13:35.550 align:middle line:84%
But putting them into practice
is another whole game.

00:13:35.550 --> 00:13:40.730 align:middle line:84%
And so they looked at
the whole issue and said,

00:13:40.730 --> 00:13:47.130 align:middle line:84%
well, if we consider a
nation like a car running

00:13:47.130 --> 00:13:50.430 align:middle line:84%
on fossil fuels, you got
the fossil fuel going in,

00:13:50.430 --> 00:13:53.290 align:middle line:84%
you can stop the engine by
squeezing off the fossil fuel

00:13:53.290 --> 00:13:54.120 align:middle line:90%
line.

00:13:54.120 --> 00:13:55.780 align:middle line:84%
But if you did that
in a nation, people

00:13:55.780 --> 00:13:56.821 align:middle line:90%
would scream immediately.

00:13:56.821 --> 00:14:01.070 align:middle line:84%
And you see that with whenever
the gasoline prices went up,

00:14:01.070 --> 00:14:03.100 align:middle line:90%
people were outraged.

00:14:03.100 --> 00:14:06.450 align:middle line:84%
But you can also stop the
engine by plugging the exhaust.

00:14:06.450 --> 00:14:10.140 align:middle line:84%
So they said, OK, what's the
byproduct of the fossil fuel

00:14:10.140 --> 00:14:10.940 align:middle line:90%
industry?

00:14:10.940 --> 00:14:13.330 align:middle line:90%
And the answer is, mostly CO2.

00:14:13.330 --> 00:14:16.772 align:middle line:84%
So they said, let's show that
CO2 is causing global warming.

00:14:16.772 --> 00:14:17.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Just make it happen.

00:14:17.980 --> 00:14:19.390 align:middle line:90%
>>BALL: Make it happen.

00:14:19.390 --> 00:14:22.290 align:middle line:84%
And what Maurice Strong
did-- and by the way,

00:14:22.290 --> 00:14:24.610 align:middle line:84%
Elaine Dewar said to him,
well, you got this idea.

00:14:24.610 --> 00:14:26.660 align:middle line:90%
Why don't you run for politics?

00:14:26.660 --> 00:14:29.160 align:middle line:84%
He made a very telling
comment when he said,

00:14:29.160 --> 00:14:31.660 align:middle line:84%
you can't do anything
as a politician.

00:14:31.660 --> 00:14:34.680 align:middle line:84%
And that, by the way,
parallels Conrad Black,

00:14:34.680 --> 00:14:36.984 align:middle line:84%
a name that Americans
are familiar with.

00:14:36.984 --> 00:14:39.400 align:middle line:84%
And they said to him one time,
why aren't you in politics?

00:14:39.400 --> 00:14:42.110 align:middle line:84%
And he said, I don't
need to be, which

00:14:42.110 --> 00:14:45.440 align:middle line:84%
is a very telling comment about
the state of politics today.

00:14:45.440 --> 00:14:47.650 align:middle line:84%
And you see that, of course,
in terms of influence

00:14:47.650 --> 00:14:49.290 align:middle line:90%
of donors and everything else.

00:14:49.290 --> 00:14:50.862 align:middle line:84%
But Elaine Dewar
said to him, well,

00:14:50.862 --> 00:14:52.570 align:middle line:84%
how are you going to
implement this idea?

00:14:52.570 --> 00:14:54.360 align:middle line:84%
And he said, I'm going to
go to the United Nations

00:14:54.360 --> 00:14:55.859 align:middle line:84%
where I can get all
the money I want

00:14:55.859 --> 00:14:57.640 align:middle line:84%
and not be accountable
to anybody.

00:14:57.640 --> 00:14:59.250 align:middle line:84%
He then went to
the United Nations

00:14:59.250 --> 00:15:01.870 align:middle line:84%
to set up the United Nations
Environment Program, which

00:15:01.870 --> 00:15:05.810 align:middle line:84%
was the Rio conference, which
George Herbert Bush said,

00:15:05.810 --> 00:15:06.765 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to it.

00:15:06.765 --> 00:15:09.939 align:middle line:84%
It's political nonsense,
and refused to go.

00:15:09.939 --> 00:15:10.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's a football.

00:15:10.980 --> 00:15:11.780 align:middle line:90%
>>BALL: Yeah.

00:15:11.780 --> 00:15:14.000 align:middle line:84%
And there, at that
conference, he

00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:17.510 align:middle line:84%
set up Agenda 21, which I
know you've done programs on.

00:15:17.510 --> 00:15:20.200 align:middle line:84%
That was the
political side of it.

00:15:20.200 --> 00:15:22.410 align:middle line:84%
And in the political side
of it with the climate,

00:15:22.410 --> 00:15:25.479 align:middle line:84%
they set up what was called
the Conference of the Parties.

00:15:25.479 --> 00:15:27.770 align:middle line:84%
Now that's a term that people
will have heard recently,

00:15:27.770 --> 00:15:30.340 align:middle line:84%
because the Paris Climate
Conference was the Conference

00:15:30.340 --> 00:15:33.710 align:middle line:90%
of the Parties number 21.

00:15:33.710 --> 00:15:37.890 align:middle line:84%
And so they determine how much
money is going to be spent

00:15:37.890 --> 00:15:41.680 align:middle line:84%
and what politics is going to
occur with regard to climate.

00:15:41.680 --> 00:15:44.680 align:middle line:84%
But they can only operate
on the basis of the science

00:15:44.680 --> 00:15:47.440 align:middle line:84%
that they're being given by
the Intergovernmental Panel

00:15:47.440 --> 00:15:50.230 align:middle line:84%
on Climate Change,
the IPCC, which

00:15:50.230 --> 00:15:53.710 align:middle line:84%
was set up through the United
Nations Framework Convention

00:15:53.710 --> 00:15:55.280 align:middle line:90%
on Climate Change.

00:15:55.280 --> 00:15:57.090 align:middle line:84%
Now, here's the
interesting thing.

00:15:57.090 --> 00:16:00.460 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to step aside
from that for a minute.

00:16:00.460 --> 00:16:03.950 align:middle line:84%
I've served on many commissions
of inquiry-- federal,

00:16:03.950 --> 00:16:06.440 align:middle line:84%
provincial, or state
level and so on.

00:16:06.440 --> 00:16:09.689 align:middle line:84%
And I used to think commissions
of inquiry were great.

00:16:09.689 --> 00:16:10.980 align:middle line:90%
And I think a lot of people do.

00:16:10.980 --> 00:16:14.400 align:middle line:84%
You finally get the politics
out of the nonsense.

00:16:14.400 --> 00:16:15.310 align:middle line:90%
Just get somebody--

00:16:15.310 --> 00:16:17.020 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But they're
run by the politicians.

00:16:17.020 --> 00:16:18.603 align:middle line:84%
>>BALL: But people
don't realize that,

00:16:18.603 --> 00:16:20.510 align:middle line:90%
and don't realize how they run.

00:16:20.510 --> 00:16:23.270 align:middle line:84%
And I found out the first
commission of inquiry

00:16:23.270 --> 00:16:26.546 align:middle line:84%
I was appointed to, because
it was dispute over a lake.

00:16:26.546 --> 00:16:27.920 align:middle line:84%
And by the way,
fights over water

00:16:27.920 --> 00:16:29.294 align:middle line:84%
are going to be
much, much more--

00:16:29.294 --> 00:16:31.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's going
to be huge, huge.

00:16:31.140 --> 00:16:32.340 align:middle line:90%
Wars will be fought.

00:16:32.340 --> 00:16:33.465 align:middle line:90%
>>BALL: And have been.

00:16:33.465 --> 00:16:34.630 align:middle line:90%
And have been.

00:16:34.630 --> 00:16:38.522 align:middle line:84%
And anyway, finally
the politicians said,

00:16:38.522 --> 00:16:40.230 align:middle line:84%
we're going to have
a commission inquiry.

00:16:40.230 --> 00:16:41.800 align:middle line:90%
Everybody cheered.

00:16:41.800 --> 00:16:43.680 align:middle line:84%
The politician's
now off the hook.

00:16:43.680 --> 00:16:46.280 align:middle line:84%
Because the media say,
well, what about this issue?

00:16:46.280 --> 00:16:48.105 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's the
committee's job.

00:16:48.105 --> 00:16:50.640 align:middle line:84%
>>BALL: Got to wait
till they reply.

00:16:50.640 --> 00:16:54.030 align:middle line:84%
Then we got the terms of
reference for the commission.

00:16:54.030 --> 00:16:57.900 align:middle line:84%
They were so limited to
pre-determine the outcome.

00:16:57.900 --> 00:17:01.147 align:middle line:84%
And I did something that
I'm actually quite proud of.

00:17:01.147 --> 00:17:03.230 align:middle line:84%
I told the chairman of the
commission, Mr. Duncan,

00:17:03.230 --> 00:17:04.930 align:middle line:84%
I said, you go
tell the minister.

00:17:04.930 --> 00:17:09.490 align:middle line:84%
Either we get carte blanche to
all of the information, nothing

00:17:09.490 --> 00:17:11.828 align:middle line:84%
hidden, or I'm going to
go to the media and say,

00:17:11.828 --> 00:17:13.369 align:middle line:84%
the minister's trying
to predetermine

00:17:13.369 --> 00:17:14.500 align:middle line:90%
the outcome of this commission.

00:17:14.500 --> 00:17:15.416 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's right.

00:17:15.416 --> 00:17:17.349 align:middle line:84%
>>BALL: Now, you
know, on your program

00:17:17.349 --> 00:17:20.339 align:middle line:84%
you deal with
conspiracy theories.

00:17:20.339 --> 00:17:23.380 align:middle line:84%
And the internet, of course,
has fostered so many of those.

00:17:23.380 --> 00:17:26.930 align:middle line:84%
One of the biggest in the
world is, who killed Kennedy?

00:17:26.930 --> 00:17:28.860 align:middle line:84%
And I know you've
talked about revisiting

00:17:28.860 --> 00:17:30.470 align:middle line:90%
that in your program.

00:17:30.470 --> 00:17:35.820 align:middle line:84%
Well, I was watching
Justice Warren one

00:17:35.820 --> 00:17:39.200 align:middle line:84%
time-- I believe it was
ABC-- before he passed away.

00:17:39.200 --> 00:17:41.230 align:middle line:84%
And the interviewer said,
well, why didn't you

00:17:41.230 --> 00:17:45.610 align:middle line:84%
look at the Dallas Mafia
connection with Jack Ruby.

00:17:45.610 --> 00:17:50.050 align:middle line:84%
And Warren said, it wasn't
in my terms of reference.

00:17:50.050 --> 00:17:51.800 align:middle line:90%
I knew what he was saying.

00:17:51.800 --> 00:17:56.970 align:middle line:84%
He was saying I was
told not to go there.

00:17:56.970 --> 00:17:58.870 align:middle line:84%
But most of the
audience, that would

00:17:58.870 --> 00:18:00.910 align:middle line:90%
have just slipped right by them.

00:18:00.910 --> 00:18:03.055 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That was the
key to the entire puzzle.

00:18:03.055 --> 00:18:05.380 align:middle line:90%
>>BALL: Exactly, exactly.

00:18:05.380 --> 00:18:08.510 align:middle line:84%
And by the way, Trump is pushing
another one now with the 9/11

00:18:08.510 --> 00:18:11.200 align:middle line:84%
inquiry, where he's saying,
what's in those 28 pages

00:18:11.200 --> 00:18:12.800 align:middle line:90%
they're not telling you?

00:18:12.800 --> 00:18:14.840 align:middle line:84%
That's where the
conspiracy theories start.

00:18:14.840 --> 00:18:18.060 align:middle line:90%
They start in the cover-up.

00:18:18.060 --> 00:18:22.050 align:middle line:84%
So when Maurice Strong set up
the Intergovernmental Panel

00:18:22.050 --> 00:18:25.820 align:middle line:84%
on Climate Change, they wrote
the definition and terms

00:18:25.820 --> 00:18:29.240 align:middle line:84%
of reference that
predetermined the outcome.

00:18:29.240 --> 00:18:30.320 align:middle line:90%
And how did they do that?

00:18:30.320 --> 00:18:33.930 align:middle line:84%
They defined and directed
them to only look

00:18:33.930 --> 00:18:36.110 align:middle line:84%
at human causes
of climate change.

00:18:36.110 --> 00:18:39.170 align:middle line:84%
In other words, don't look
at any of the natural causes.

00:18:39.170 --> 00:18:40.490 align:middle line:90%
Just look at the human causes.

00:18:40.490 --> 00:18:42.420 align:middle line:84%
Well, you can't
possibly determine

00:18:42.420 --> 00:18:45.020 align:middle line:84%
any possible human causes
if you don't know what

00:18:45.020 --> 00:18:46.870 align:middle line:90%
the natural consequences are.

00:18:46.870 --> 00:18:50.520 align:middle line:90%
So it really narrowed it down.

00:18:50.520 --> 00:18:55.590 align:middle line:84%
And just to give you an example,
CO2 as a greenhouse gas-- and I

00:18:55.590 --> 00:18:58.720 align:middle line:84%
debate whether it is
even one-- it's only 4%

00:18:58.720 --> 00:19:00.570 align:middle line:90%
of the total greenhouse gases.

00:19:00.570 --> 00:19:04.000 align:middle line:90%
Water vapor is 95%.

00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:06.870 align:middle line:84%
What does the Intergovernmental
Panel on Climate Change do?

00:19:06.870 --> 00:19:10.350 align:middle line:84%
They said, well, water vapor,
humans produce a little,

00:19:10.350 --> 00:19:14.080 align:middle line:84%
but it's so insignificant
compared to the total.

00:19:14.080 --> 00:19:16.500 align:middle line:84%
We're going to
assume it's constant.

00:19:16.500 --> 00:19:18.040 align:middle line:90%
How can you do that?

00:19:18.040 --> 00:19:20.280 align:middle line:84%
Because the variance
in water vapor

00:19:20.280 --> 00:19:23.490 align:middle line:84%
each year more than
swamps any possible effect

00:19:23.490 --> 00:19:25.650 align:middle line:84%
that CO2 changes
might be having.

00:19:25.650 --> 00:19:28.080 align:middle line:84%
But because their
terms of reference

