Peter Gleich, who is involved
in the global warming issue

00:39:36.720 --> 00:39:39.940 align:middle line:10%
out at Stanford, he's now
coined the phrase "peak water."

00:39:39.940 --> 00:39:41.095 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I like that.

00:39:41.095 --> 00:39:43.070 align:middle line:90%
That one could be real.

00:39:43.070 --> 00:39:45.170 align:middle line:84%
There is no peak
oil, but water--

00:39:45.170 --> 00:39:47.430 align:middle line:84%
we got to make sure
people can treat water.

00:39:47.430 --> 00:39:49.500 align:middle line:84%
>>BALL: But it's the
greatest deception history.

00:39:49.500 --> 00:39:50.620 align:middle line:90%
There's no question about that.

00:39:50.620 --> 00:39:51.290 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Thanks for
being on the program.

00:39:51.290 --> 00:39:52.850 align:middle line:84%
>>BALL: Thank you for
the opportunity, George.

00:39:52.850 --> 00:39:55.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Folks, regardless
of your belief system

00:39:55.030 --> 00:39:57.100 align:middle line:84%
of climate change,
there's no doubt

00:39:57.100 --> 00:39:59.400 align:middle line:84%
that things are
happening on this planet.

00:39:59.400 --> 00:40:01.270 align:middle line:84%
The only advice I
could give you is

00:40:01.270 --> 00:40:04.320 align:middle line:84%
listen to people like Dr.
Tim Ball, who are telling you

00:40:04.320 --> 00:40:05.640 align:middle line:90%
the way they see it.

00:40:05.640 --> 00:40:07.920 align:middle line:10%
And then you make up
your own mind as well.

00:40:07.920 --> 00:40:11.460 align:middle line:10%
I'm George Noory, and thanks
for watching "Beyond Belief."

